 :tx/rationale "ATT-2 DEEP SPEC: SURPRISAL COMPUTATION. Given the cache file, the surprisal for a block with label L is: surprisal(L) = 1.0 / sqrt(max(1, counts[L])). Properties: (1) BOUNDED: surprisal in (0, 1]. Never zero (the block always has SOME information value). Never > 1 (first presentation is the maximum). (2) MONOTONE DECREASING: surprisal(N) > surprisal(N+1) for all N >= 1. (3) CONVEX: the marginal decrease in surprisal diminishes with each presentation. The 2nd presentation drops from 1.0 to 0.71 (29% drop). The 10th drops from 0.33 to 0.32 (3% drop). This models the fact that the FIRST repetition teaches the most, and subsequent repetitions have diminishing returns. (4) PARAMETERIZABLE: 1/sqrt(N) is the PRIOR. The exponent (currently 0.5) is itself a learnable parameter at Level 4 of the fractal tower. Stored as :attention/decay-exponent (Double, default 0.5). The verbose-request signal calibrates it: frequent verbose requests after few presentations → exponent too high (decay too fast). No verbose requests ever → exponent too low (decay too slow)."
